title: Chinese e-commerce giant sets up first U.S. office in Santa Clara
text:
Photo: Connor Radnovich, The Chronicle Chen Zhang, senior vice president, laughs during Rain Long's speech during the opening of JD.com's new headquarters in Santa Clara, California, on Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. Chen Zhang, senior vice president, laughs during Rain Long's speech...
For Chinese e-commerce company JD.com, recruiting tech talent from Chinese universities can be a challenge when you’re competing against the likes of Google and Facebook.
